{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id785b58da-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s611a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"611a"},"text":"§ 611a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Permits to cut and remove timber; citizens of Bear Lake County, Idaho","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary of the Interior is authorized to grant permits, subject to the provisions of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s607"},"text":"section 607 of this title","children":[],"tail":", to citizens of Bear Lake County, Idaho, to cut and remove timber on the unappropriated public domain in Lincoln County, Wyoming, for domestic use in Bear Lake County, Idaho: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided","children":[],"tail":", That no live standing timber shall be taken without compensation."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id785b58db-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1891-03-03/ch561/s8"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1891, ch. 561, § 8","children":[],"tail":" (part), as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-21/ch591"},"text":"Aug. 21, 1935, ch. 591","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/665"},"text":"49 Stat. 665","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id785b58dc-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id785b58dd-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id785b58de-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is derived from act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1935-08-01"},"text":"Aug. 1, 1935","children":[],"tail":", which recites that it amends section 8 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1891-03-31"},"text":"Mar. 31, 1891","children":[],"tail":", which is the source of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s607"},"text":"section 607 of this title","children":[],"tail":", by adding this section thereto. Section 8 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1891-03-03"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1891","children":[],"tail":", is classified to sections 607, 608 to 611a of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
